as getting experience from mobs, it seems to me that<br>
for melee skillups it's more of a flat level range (ie the<br>
mob cannot be more than, say, 10 levels below you)<br>
whereas the guidelines for a mob being DB/LB/green<br>
are related more to a percentage of the PC's level, which<br>
would explain why at lower levels you can still skill up<br>
defens on LB mobs, but at higher levels (for me around the<br>
late 40's) skillups seemed only to occur on dark blue mobs.<br>
<br>
not exactly sure, just a general impression. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub199.ezboard.com/bcolossusoflanys.showUserPublicProfile?gid=newbus>Newbus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#330000>(4/30/03 8:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub199.ezboard.com/fcolossusoflanysfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: neat trick for maxing defense if anyone's interested.</span><hr size=1> that would definitely make sense <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
